Accommodation – Their affirmative creates an Indian theme park, where you can vote for Indians and be a good liberal for 2 hours at a time. However, this is enacted without ever dealing meaningfully with Indian scholarship – it’s what Churchill describes when he says liberals say &amp;#34;Yes, that’s important too&amp;#34; but then puts indigenous issues on the back-burner. Within the debate context, this is nothing more than accommodation.&#xD;
&#xD;
Sandy Grande. Red Pedagogy: Native American Social and Political Thought. 2004. Page 92-93.&#xD;
&#xD;
Indeed, various critical scholars have revealed &amp;#34;essentialism&amp;#34; as an integral part of &#xD;
AND&#xD;
the First Universal Races Conference with W.E.B. Dubois.&amp;#34;&#xD;
&#xD;
The affirmative’s reduction of radical alterity to difference points to a complicity in a system of accommodate or banish – in this paradigm, the radical other must be exterminated. They can either destroy themselves by assimilating into the system of difference, the flows of affect, or they will face destruction at the hands of those who wish to integrate them.&#xD;
