**A - - Death is a rendezvous, not an objective destiny. The more we try to escape fate, the more we seem to run to it.  Baudrillard explains in 2001  **(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:8.0pt;line-height:115%&amp;#34; %)(//Seduction//, 2001, p. 72-74)

