(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNoSpacing&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;margin-left:.5in&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:7.0pt&amp;#34; %)An ellipsis of the sign, an eclipse of meaning: an, illusion. The mortal distraction that (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;background:fuchsia; mso-highlight:fuchsia&amp;#34; %)a(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size: 7.0pt&amp;#34; %) single sign can cause instantaneously. (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__Consider the story of the __(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__soldier__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__ __(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__who __(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__meets Death at__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__ __(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__a crossing in __(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__the__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__ (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %)market(%%)__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__place, __(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__and believes he saw__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__ __(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__him make __(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__a menacing gesture__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__ __(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__in his direction__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: lime; mso-highlight: lime&amp;#34; %)__.__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__ __(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__He rushes to the__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__ (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %)king(%%)__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__&amp;#39;s palace __(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__and asks__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__ __(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__the king __(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__for his__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__ __(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__best __(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__horse__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__ __(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__in order that he might flee during the night far from Death, as far as Samarkand. Upon which __(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__the king summons Death__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__ __(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__to the palace __(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__and reproaches him__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__ __(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__for having frightened one of his best servants. ; But __(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__Death__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__, astonished, __(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__replies__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__: __(% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: lime; mso-highlight: lime&amp;#34; %)__&amp;#34;__(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__I didn&amp;#39;t mean to frighten him . It was just that I was surprised to see this__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__ (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; %)soldier here, when we had a rendez-vous tomorrow(%%) __(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__in Samarkand__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt&amp;#34; %). &amp;#34; (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__Yes, __(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__one runs towards one&amp;#39;s fate all the more surely by seeking to escape it__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__ __(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__.__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt&amp;#34; %) (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__Yes, everyone seeks his own death, and the failed acts are the most successful __(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %). (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:9.0pt&amp;#34; %)Yes, signs follow an unconscious course. But all this concerns the truth of the rendez-vous in Samarkand; it does not account for the seduction of the story, which is in no way an apologue of truth(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt&amp;#34; %). (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__What is astounding about the story is that this seemingly inevitable rendez-vous need not have taken place. There is nothing to suggest that the soldier would have been in Samarkand without this chance encounter, and without the ill-luck of Death&amp;#39;s naive gesture, which acted in spite of itself as a gesture of seduction. Had Death been content to call the soldier back to order, the story would lose its charm. Everything here is hinged on a single, involuntary sign.__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__The gesture__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) does not appear to be part of a strategy, nor even an unconscious ruse; yet it (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__takes on the unexpected depth of seduction, that is, it appears as something that moves laterally, as a sign that, unbeknownst to the protagonists (including Death, as well as the soldier), advances a deadly command, an aleatory sign behind which another conjunction, marvelous or disastrous, is being enacted.__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) A conjunction that gives the sign&amp;#39;s trajectory all the characteristics of a witticism . No one in the story has anything to reproach himself with -or else the king who lent his horse, is as guilty as anyone else. No. (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__Behind the apparent liberty of the two central characters (Death was free to make his gesture, the soldier to flee), they were both following a rule of which neither were aware__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %). (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__The rule of this game__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %), which, like every fundamental rule, must remain secret, (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__is that **death is not a brute event**__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt&amp;#34; %), (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__but only occurs through seduction, that is, by way of an instantaneous, indecipherable complicity, by a sign or signs that will not be deciphered in time. **Death is a rendez-vous, not an objective destiny**__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt&amp;#34; %). (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__Death cannot fail to go since he is this rendez-vous, that is, the allusive conjunction of signs and rules which make up the-game__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %). (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__At the same time, Death is an innocent player in the game. This is what gives the story its secret irony, whose resolution appears as a stroke of wit__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 6.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %) trait d esprit, (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__and provides us with such sublime pleasure - and distinguishes it from a moral fable or a vulgar tale about the death instinct__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt&amp;#34; %). The spiritual character trait spirituel of the story extends the spirited character trait d espritgestuel of Death&amp;#39;s gesture, and (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__the two seductions, that of Death and of the story, fuse together__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %). (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__Death&amp;#39;s astonishment is delightful, an astonishment at the frivolity of an arrangement where things proceed **by chance** : &amp;#34;But this soldier should have known that he was expected in Samarkand tomorrow, and taken his time to get there__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %). . .&amp;#34; (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__However __(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__Death shows only surprise, as if his existence did not depend as much as the soldier&amp;#39;s on the fact that they were to meet__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)__** **__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__**in Samarkand**__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %). (% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt;background:fuchsia;mso-highlight:fuchsia&amp;#34; %)Death(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;background:fuchsia;mso-highlight:fuchsia&amp;#34; %)**__ __**(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)**__lets things happen__**(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %), (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__and it is his casualness that makes him appealing - this is why the soldier hastens to join him. __(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)None of this involves the unconscious, metaphysics or psychology. Or even strategy. (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)**__Death __**(% class=&amp;#34;StyleBoldUnderline&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;font-size: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12pt; background: fuchsia; mso-highlight: fuchsia&amp;#34; %)**__has no plan__**(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %). (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__He restores chance with a **chance gesture**; this is how he works, yet everything still gets done. There is nothing that cannot not be done, yet everything still preserves the lightness of chance, of a furtive gesture, an accidental encounter or an illegible sign. That&amp;#39;s how it is with seduction__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %). . . (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__Moreover, the soldier went to meet death because he gave meaning to a meaningless gesture which did not even concern him. He took personally something that was not addressed to him, as one might mistake for oneself a smile meant for someone else__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %). The height of seduction is to be without seduction. (% style=&amp;#34;font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt&amp;#34; %)__The man seduced is caught in spite of himself in a web of stray signs. And it is because the sign has been turned from its meaning or &amp;#34;seduced,&amp;#34; that the story itself is seductive__(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:6.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt&amp;#34; %). It is when signs are seduced that they become seductive.

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNoSpacing&amp;#34; %)
