=== This means that financial crisises will be inevitable, but not on a cataclysmic scale, but in local, episodic ways. The current recession didn&amp;#39;t loosen wall streets grip on the economy, it just hurt the American middle class. The same thing happens when we try and steer the market in a particular direction; theres no way to guarantee the outcome, but theres a higher risk we will not change a dman thing ===

